[2026-03-18T18:02:47.589Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Replace O(n) trigger scan with priority queue\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: maintenance\n- **Effort**: Unknown (4/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (6/3)\n- **Scan Type**: insight_synth\n- **Generated**: 3/18/2026, 9:37:05 AM\n\n## Description\nThe scheduler calls getDueTriggers every 5 seconds, scanning all enabled triggers against datetime now. Replace this with an in-memory min-heap keyed by next_trigger_at. On each tick, pop entries whose time has passed. Rebuild the heap on startup from the DB, and update it on trigger CRUD operations. The DB remains the source of truth but the hot path avoids full table scans.\n\n## Reasoning\nThe current O(n) scan works at small scale but becomes a bottleneck as trigger count grows. The architectural shift from polling-a-table to draining-a-queue reveals that the scheduler is really an event-sourced timeline, simplifying reasoning about ordering, missed triggers, and batch processing.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\n- **compact-ui-design**: Use `.claude/skills/compact-ui-design.md` for high-quality UI design references and patterns\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done